                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <origDate notBefore="1900" notAfter="1950" evidence="context"/>
                            The manuscript was copied from an exemplar in <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0005Gund">Gunda Gunde</placeName>. The catalogue refers to <bibl><seg type="journalArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Mordini1953GG"/><title level="a">Il convento di Gunde Gundiè</title><title level="j">Rassegna di Studi Etiopici</title><author><forename>Antonio</forename><surname>Mordini</surname></author><date>1953</date><biblScope unit="volume">12</biblScope><biblScope unit="page">29-70</biblScope><note type="url">http://www.jstor.org/stable/41460274</note><note type="tags"><note type="tag">Monastery</note><note type="tag">Collection</note><note type="tag">bm:Mordini1953GG</note><note type="tag">Gunda Gunde</note></note><note type="tag">Monastery</note><note type="tag">Collection</note><note type="tag">bm:Mordini1953GG</note><note type="tag">Gunda Gunde</note><citedRange unit="50"/></bibl> and proposes
                            the two manuscripts Mordini no. 103 or Mordini no. 146 (<ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/GG00002">ኢሮብ፡, Gunda Gunde, C3-IV-149</ref>) as potential
                            exemplars. A cursory comparison with <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/GG00002">ኢሮብ፡, Gunda Gunde, C3-IV-149</ref> supports this hypothesis.                        
                        </origin>
                        <acquisition>The manuscript passed into the possession of the library in <date when="1950">1950</date>, following Conti Rossini’s death in <date when="1949">1949</date> 
                            (see <ref target="https://www.menestrel.fr/?-Roma-&amp;lang=fr#845">Menestrel</ref>).</acquisition>
                    </history>
                    
